{"expand":"renderedFields,names,schema,transitions,operations,editmeta,changelog","id":"45091","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/latest/issue/45091","key":"PLXCOMP-19","fields":{"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"summary":"When forking javac, receive \"The input line is too long\" error from Windows","timetracking":{},"issuetype":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issuetype/1","id":"1","description":"A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png","name":"Bug","subtask":false},"customfield_10110":null,"votes":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issue/PLXCOMP-19/votes","votes":1,"hasVoted":false},"resolution":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/resolution/1","id":"1","description":"A fix for this issue is checked into the tree and tested.","name":"Fixed"},"fixVersions":[],"resolutiondate":"2007-01-10T18:57:18.847-0600","customfield_10210":"2.0","timespent":null,"reporter":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/user?username=eghchang","name":"eghchang","emailAddress":"eghchang@gmail.com","avatarUrls":{"16x16":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10232","24x24":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10232","32x32":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10232","48x48":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10232"},"displayName":"Eric Chang","active":true},"aggregatetimeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_10161":["carlos(carlos)","eghchang(eghchang)"],"customfield_10160":null,"updated":"2007-01-14T13:48:40.408-0600","created":"2006-12-20T14:15:57.970-0600","description":"Hello,\n\nI'm using maven 2.0.4 and the following configuration for the maven-compiler-plugin (which appears to have a transitive dependency on 1.5.2 plexus-compiler-javac):\n\n            <plugin>\n                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n                <version>2.0.1</version>\n                <configuration>\n                    <fork>true</fork>\n                    <source>1.5</source>\n                    <target>1.5</target>\n                    <executable>${jdk1.5.0_10}/bin/javac</executable>\n                    <compilerVersion>1.5</compilerVersion>\n                </configuration>\n            </plugin>\n\nWhen I ran \"mvn clean compile\", I encounter the following error:\n\nCompiling 36 source files to C:\\projects\\src\\soap\\soap-model\\target\\classes\n[INFO] ------------------------------------------------------------------------\n[ERROR] BUILD FAILURE\n[INFO] ------------------------------------------------------------------------\n[INFO] Compilation failure\n\nFailure executing javac,  but could not parse the error:\n\n\n[INFO] ------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nI pulled the 1.5.2 plexus-compiler-javac code and threw in some debug statements to output the forked command line process.  In this case, CommandLineUtils is being invoked with a 8,172-character-long command line.  When I try to run this command line in a windows cmd window, I get the error \"The input line is too long\".\n\nI believe this is happening because the AbstractCompiler.getSourceFiles() scans a CompilerConfiguration.getSourceLocations() and builds an explicit list of all of the java files.  I think if this would instead use the \"-sourcepath\" javac option, that would reduce the verbosity of the generated command line.","priority":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/priorities/major.png","name":"Major","id":"3"},"duedate":null,"issuelinks":[{"id":"15648","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issueLink/15648","type":{"id":"10001","name":"dependent","inward":"is depended upon by","outward":"depends upon","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issueLinkTy